Colleagues of Father Emmanuel Silas realised that he had been abducted after he didn't show up for mass on Monday morning. Over the weekend two Catholic priests were abducted in the southern state of Edo, and last week a priest was taken from his home near the city of Auchi in the same region and later found dead. The security services in Nigeria are struggling to combat an upsurge in criminal killings and kidnappings for ransom across the country. --BBC--